Explanation:

- The route configuration (routes/api.php) registers an apiResource for "media" under the /v1 prefix and places the store and destroy actions behind the auth:sanctum and verified middleware. Therefore the DELETE /v1/media/{media} endpoint requires authentication via Sanctum.
- The controller method is MediaController@destroy. In app/Http/Controllers/Api/V1/MediaController.php the destroy method signature is destroy(Media $medium): Response. That indicates the route parameter {media} is route-model-bound to the Media model (so the parameter represents a media resource identifier). The method calls $this->authorize('delete', $medium) (so an authorization check is performed) and then $medium->delete(); finally it returns response()->noContent(), which produces an HTTP 204 No Content on success.
- Based on these observations, the OpenAPI Operation Object for DELETE /v1/media/{media} should:
  - Indicate it requires authentication (Sanctum).
  - Include a required path parameter "media" (ID of the media to delete).
  - List responses for success (204 No Content) and common error statuses related to auth/permissions/not-found (401, 403, 404).

